          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The point describing the position of the hot spot, specified according to the cursor’s flipped coordinate system. For a more complete explanation of a cursor’s hot spot, see the class overview."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Note that an "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSCursor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object is immutable: you cannot change its hot spot after it’s created. Instead, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscursor/1524612-initwithimage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to create a new cursor with the new settings."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
